critique: This document is a land withdrawal order from 1933, signed by the President. It withdraws public lands in New Mexico from settlement, location, sale, entry, and all forms of appropriation pending a resurvey. This seems to be a fairly routine administrative action related to land management. There's no clear indication of a liberal or conservative ideological tilt. It doesn't directly address immigration. It could be argued that withdrawing land expands executive power, but it's within the bounds of existing legislation. It centralizes control over these lands at the federal level. It doesn't directly impact national security or civil liberties. It has a minor impact on economic regulation by restricting land use. It doesn't seem to have a significant impact on social inclusion.
